Day in Donbass: 15 enemy shelling, two Allied soldiers wounded

03 Nov 2019, 05:46

The invaders fired at rocket-propelled grenades, machine-guns and small arms
On Saturday, November 2, fighters in Donbass 15 times violated the ceasefire regime.
The enemy fired on the positions of the units of the Joint Forces with the prohibited Minsk agreements of 120 mm mortars, as well as grenade launchers of various systems, large machine guns and other small arms.
This is stated in the morning news release of the United Forces operation.
In the area of responsibility of the tactical group "East" the enemy carried out six shellings:

near Novogrigorovka - 120 mm mortars;
near Avdiivka - with RPGs, automatic grenade launchers, large machine guns and small arms;
nearby Talakivka - with automatic grenade launchers;
twice in the vicinity of the Water, which in the Azov region - with automatic grenade launchers and large machine guns;
near Pavopol - from small arms.

In the area of responsibility of the tactical group "North" the enemy fired nine shots:

near Novozanovka - hand-held anti-tank and automatic grenade launchers;
three times near Novolugansk - from small arms and machine guns anti-tank and automatic grenade launchers;
twice near Free Farm - with small arms;
nearby Lugansk - large-caliber machine guns and hand anti-tank grenade launchers;
near Shumov - from anti-tank grenade launchers and small arms;
near Zaitsev - with LNG, small arms and automatic grenade launchers.

Yesterday, November 2, two U.S. Army personnel were injured by the shelling.
From the beginning of this era, the armed forces of the Russian Federation and its mercenaries did not show any fire activity.
